%N A395952 a(n) is the largest integer k < 2^(n-1) for which the number of divisors is equal to n, or 0 if no such k exists.
%C A395952 a(n) = 0 if n is noncomposite (A008578) and a(n) > 0 if n is composite (A002808).
%C A395952 For prime p, A000005(p^(n-1)) = n.
%H A395952 Daniel Suteu, <a href="/A395952/b395952.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..80</a>
%o A395952 (PARI) list(len) = {my(v = vector(len), n); for(k = 1, 2^(len-1), n = numdiv(k); if(n <= len && k < 2^(n-1), v[n] = k)); v;} \\ _Amiram Eldar_, May 13 2026
%o A395952 (PARI) a(n) = if(n<=1 || isprime(n), return(0)); forstep(k=2^(n-1)-1, 1, -1, if(numdiv(k) == n, return(k))); \\ _Daniel Suteu_, May 18 2026
%Y A395952 Superset of A000396.
